<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-13T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-13T23:00:00-05:00" n="903" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d903">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/604a: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-14T00:00:00-04:00">April 14,
                                1943—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2378. To Casaday from White. Secretary Morgenthau is arranging schedule for
                        discussions with technical experts of preliminary draft outline of proposal
                        for international stabilization fund. Secretary would like you to inquire of
                        finance ministers of exiled governments except French National Committee
                        when their experts may be expected for discussions and whom they expect to
                        send. [White.]</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>